divs: Sighting Details1. I was the Captain of a commercial airliner. 2. The contrail of another aircraft. 3. Unknown 4. Very small metallic stationary object at very high altitude, possibly rectangular. 5. Pointed it out to the First Officer, who also saw it. Queried air traffic control. ATC then proceeded to ask us a few questions, mainly if was moving and and est. alitude. ATC then contacted the military to query them if they had anything up there, to which they responded that they didn't. 6. Got busy in the flight and job duties at hand took priority.
